n borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Heinrich Bertold I von Neuffen was born about 1176, in Neuffen, Nürtingen, Württemberg, Germany, his father, Berthold Von Neuffen II, was 25 and his mother, Adelheid von Achalm, was 21. He married Adelheid von Winnenden. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died after 1246, in his hometown."},"et":{"um 1176–after 1246":"umbes 1176–pärast 1246","1176–1246":"1176–1246","1186–1246":"1186–1246","1180–Female":"1180–Surnud","1199–Female":"1199–Surnud","1218–1278":"1218–1278","1152–1221":"1152–1221","1156–1209":"1156–1209","1176":"1176","1175":"1175","1186":"1186","1152":"1152","1180":"1180","um 1176":"umbes 1176","1246":"1246","1278":"1278","1156":"1156","10 March 1209":"10. märts 1209","1221":"1221","1199":"1199","um 1199":"umbes 1199","1209":"1209","1218":"1218","after 1246":"pärast 1246","Neuffen, Winnenden":"Neuffen, Nürtingen, Württemberg, Saksamaa","Neuffen, Württemberg":"Neuffen, Württemberg","Neuffen, Esslingen, Baden-Wuerttemberg, Germany":"Neuffen, Landkreis Esslingen, Baden-Württemberg, Saksamaa","Neuffen, Nürtingen, Württemberg, Germany":"Neuffen, Nürtingen, Württemberg, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"um 1176–after 1246":"noin 1176–1246 jälkeen","1176–1246":"1176–1246","1186–1246":"1186–1246","1180–Female":"1180–Kuollut","1199–Female":"1199–Kuollut","1218–1278":"1218–1278","1152–1221":"1152–1221","1156–1209":"1156–1209","1176":"1176","1175":"1175","1186":"1186","1152":"1152","1180":"1180","um 1176":"noin 1176","1246":"1246","1278":"1278","1156":"1156","10 March 1209":"10. maaliskuuta 1209","1221":"1221","1199":"1199","um 1199":"noin 1199","1209":"1209","1218":"1218","after 1246":"1246 jälkeen","Neuffen, Winnenden":"Neuffen, Nürtingen, Württemberg, Saksa","Neuffen, Württemberg":"Neuffen, Württe